text:
e="preserve">Hurricane Zeta was an October 2020 Atlantic hurricane. It was the record fifth storm to hit the Gulf States. The storm hit the Mexican Yucatán Peninsula and then Louisiana and Mississippi.
Zeta had winds of 110 miles an hour when it hit the Gulf States.
The remnants of Zeta dumped snow on the New England area.
The storm left just over 2.1 million customers without power.
